1
00:01:28,940 --> 00:01:35,660
Winter Begonia

2
00:01:35,660 --> 00:01:38,060
Episode 16

3
00:01:38,979 --> 00:01:40,140
Mr. Cheng is away now.

4
00:01:40,259 --> 00:01:41,700
No one here to guide us.

5
00:01:42,460 --> 00:01:43,460
Don’t even mention him.

6
00:01:43,460 --> 00:01:44,900
Can’t find him anywhere.

7
00:01:45,220 --> 00:01:46,700
What do you think he can do?

8
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:51,820
How’s everything, ladies and gentlemen?

9
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:53,900
Is Mr. Shang here?

10
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:55,539
You still have the nerve to come here.

11
00:01:55,539 --> 00:01:56,300
Tell us,

12
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:58,020
did you or did you not help Jiang Rongshou

13
00:01:58,020 --> 00:01:58,979
bully our leader in the Association?

14
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:00,740
What an unnecessary question.

15
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:02,380
Jiang Rongshou is his uncle.

16
00:02:02,380 --> 00:02:03,460
They are birds of a feather.

17
00:02:03,460 --> 00:02:04,460
Now you got me wronged.

18
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:06,340
For God sakes,

19
00:02:06,340 --> 00:02:07,580
I helped him.

20
00:02:07,980 --> 00:02:09,620
You helped our leader?

21
00:02:09,620 --> 00:02:10,500
Hard to believe that.

22
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:12,420
I did, I really did.

23
00:02:12,820 --> 00:02:14,020
And I got kicked out afterwards.

24
00:02:14,020 --> 00:02:15,020
We will kick you out too.

25
00:02:15,020 --> 00:02:15,660
Dasheng.

26
00:02:16,060 --> 00:02:17,180
-Leave. Get out.
-Mr. Chen.

27
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:19,060
-Please get out of here.
-What do you mean?

28
00:02:19,260 --> 00:02:20,180
So rude, so rude.

29
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:20,860
So rude…

30
00:02:20,860 --> 00:02:22,140
-Let him in.
-You are so rude.

31
00:02:24,020 --> 00:02:25,100
Did you hear that?

32
00:02:35,860 --> 00:02:37,260
I thought

33
00:02:38,020 --> 00:02:40,260
we could play to our strengths

34
00:02:40,620 --> 00:02:41,980
and achieve success.

35
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:43,500
I didn’t expect that

36
00:02:44,460 --> 00:02:45,860
I would mess up with the opera

37
00:02:46,780 --> 00:02:48,220
and you mess up with people.

38
00:02:48,940 --> 00:02:50,420
Now none of us ended up well.

39
00:02:52,220 --> 00:02:53,820
To hell with that.

40
00:02:55,820 --> 00:02:57,380
I can’t believe you said that.

41
00:02:58,180 --> 00:02:59,660
Just you and me.

42
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:02,020
Why would I bother putting on airs?

43
00:03:02,540 --> 00:03:03,700
You want to see me like that?

44
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:04,740
Nope.

45
00:03:06,380 --> 00:03:07,420
To be honest,

46
00:03:07,580 --> 00:03:09,660
you look like a fool when

47
00:03:09,660 --> 00:03:11,220
you put on airs.

48
00:03:11,540 --> 00:03:13,020
I like the way you look now.

49
00:03:15,740 --> 00:03:17,180
Life is a play.

50
00:03:18,660 --> 00:03:20,220
I have to keep myself that way

51
00:03:20,660 --> 00:03:22,020
on and off stage.

52
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:23,500
Answer me.

53
00:03:24,860 --> 00:03:26,740
How did you get up the courage

54
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:28,700
to mess up with your uncle?

55
00:03:32,579 --> 00:03:35,340
Since I was thirteen,

56
00:03:36,140 --> 00:03:37,860
I have had to feed my widowed mother.

57
00:03:39,140 --> 00:03:40,380
I could live off performing operas

58
00:03:40,940 --> 00:03:42,300
because of the help from Jiang.

59
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:44,140
I had never had

60
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:45,660
disobeyed my uncle’s orders.

61
00:03:48,340 --> 00:03:49,300
I’ve had enough of it.

62
00:04:00,660 --> 00:04:01,620
What?

63
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:05,220
What?

64
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:12,660
What are you doing?

65
00:04:14,180 --> 00:04:16,500
I like playing with others’ heads.

66
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:18,940
This is funny.

67
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:24,940
Can’t you make it proper?

68
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:25,940
You got the back to the front.

69
00:04:29,420 --> 00:04:30,460
You depend others for a living.

70
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,300
Everyone got hang-ups.

71
00:04:34,020 --> 00:04:35,540
You lost the competition.

72
00:04:36,020 --> 00:04:37,780
What are you gonna do?

73
00:04:38,380 --> 00:04:39,580
No performance of opera for one year.

74
00:04:40,420 --> 00:04:41,780
Kicked out of Jiang Family.

75
00:04:43,980 --> 00:04:45,220
I’m going to Shanghai.

76
00:04:46,380 --> 00:04:48,260
Today I came to say goodbye.

77
00:04:53,140 --> 00:04:54,060
Actually it’s because

78
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:55,100
my girlfriend is in Shanghai.

79
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:58,260
Congratulations

80
00:04:58,500 --> 00:04:59,820
for your love affair.

81
00:05:00,980 --> 00:05:01,860
How about you?

82
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:04,180
I can’t imagine

83
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:05,260
those rumors spread

84
00:05:05,460 --> 00:05:06,820
on tabloids or among our peers.

85
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:09,460
Such a Spring Festival fiasco.

86
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:12,700
How about this,

87
00:05:13,940 --> 00:05:15,460
you could go to Shanghai with me.

88
00:05:16,380 --> 00:05:17,300
It’s not cold there in winter.

89
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:18,620
You will spend a green winter.

90
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:20,100
The place is prosperous.

91
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:21,060
I can introduce

92
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:23,220
you a girlfriend there.

93
00:05:29,140 --> 00:05:30,700
Forget about girlfriend.

94
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:33,780
But going to Shanghai with you

95
00:05:33,780 --> 00:05:34,820
sounds good.

96
00:05:35,780 --> 00:05:36,980
Great.

97
00:05:37,140 --> 00:05:38,620
Think about it. Others aside,

98
00:05:39,140 --> 00:05:41,580
both of us leaving here

99
00:05:42,020 --> 00:05:43,460
is enough

100
00:05:43,659 --> 00:05:45,060
to upset my uncle.

101
00:05:54,460 --> 00:05:58,380
(Peking Times)

102
00:05:59,300 --> 00:06:00,140
Get out of the way.

103
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,620
What’s the rush?

104
00:06:02,780 --> 00:06:03,340
Right.

105
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,300
Is there anyone alive?

106
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:08,860
Mr. Du.

107
00:06:08,860 --> 00:06:10,380
Come out, anyone who is alive.

108
00:06:11,420 --> 00:06:11,980
Mr. Du.

109
00:06:11,980 --> 00:06:13,140
What happened?

110
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:14,580
Why did you drop

111
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,300
my column arbitrarily?

112
00:06:17,860 --> 00:06:18,940
Who told you to do so?

113
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:21,980
Did you forget how

114
00:06:21,980 --> 00:06:23,620
you begged me to write for you

115
00:06:23,820 --> 00:06:24,980
back then?

116
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:27,100
We don’t know.

117
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:28,300
I have no idea.

118
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,180
None of us dare to do so.

119
00:06:31,180 --> 00:06:31,980
Mr. Du.

120
00:06:31,980 --> 00:06:33,340
Stop the grumbling

121
00:06:33,820 --> 00:06:35,020
and muttering.

122
00:06:35,980 --> 00:06:37,420
Find someone who can talk.

123
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,060
I don’t know.

124
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:43,020
Mr. Du.

125
00:06:43,659 --> 00:06:45,220
Our leaders made the decision.

126
00:06:45,420 --> 00:06:46,980
You have written for the column

127
00:06:46,980 --> 00:06:48,659
for more than half a year.

128
00:06:48,659 --> 00:06:50,100
It’s all about reviews of theatric performance.

129
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:52,100
People don’t read that.

130
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:54,820
So our newspaper wants a change.

131
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:56,300
A change?

132
00:06:57,580 --> 00:07:00,140
Please change to someone better than me.

133
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:02,340
What rubbish

134
00:07:03,020 --> 00:07:04,860
is this?

135
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:08,100
I can do better even with my feet.

136
00:07:08,740 --> 00:07:10,060
Well,

137
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:13,020
Mr. Du,

138
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:16,300
His literary talent is lame.

139
00:07:16,780 --> 00:07:17,300
However,

140
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:18,980
the story is dramatic

141
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:20,340
and has more fun than yours.

142
00:07:20,420 --> 00:07:22,300
People love reading this kind of articles.

143
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:23,980
-Right. We need to sell the newspaper.
-Yeah.

144
00:07:23,980 --> 00:07:24,340
Yeah.

145
00:07:24,340 --> 00:07:25,740
We make a living off the newspaper.

146
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,820
Dramatic?

147
00:07:29,980 --> 00:07:32,860
You think rumors dramatic?

148
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:33,620
Rumors?

149
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:34,940
There is no rumor.

150
00:07:34,980 --> 00:07:35,820
All content of our newspaper

151
00:07:36,380 --> 00:07:37,100
is based on truth.

152
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,620
-Right. Absolutely.
-We have started no rumors.

153
00:07:39,180 --> 00:07:39,820
Truth?

154
00:07:41,140 --> 00:07:42,860
Open your ears.

155
00:07:42,860 --> 00:07:44,180
Listen carefully.

156
00:07:47,420 --> 00:07:48,540
“Shang Xirui,

157
00:07:49,140 --> 00:07:50,260
in the gathering,

158
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:53,100
coquetted

159
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:55,380
and acted like a fool.

160
00:07:55,380 --> 00:07:58,100
The way he behaved is so coy.

161
00:07:58,300 --> 00:08:03,100
President Jiang kindly pointed that out,

162
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:05,220
yet he who is so ungrateful

163
00:08:05,420 --> 00:08:07,740
beat and kicked Chairman Jiang.”

164
00:08:08,060 --> 00:08:09,580
Bullshit.

165
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:10,140
Mr. Du.

166
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:13,340
If Shang Xirui kicked Jiang Rongshou,

167
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:15,700
do you think Jiang could stay alive?

168
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:18,940
Stop laughing.

169
00:08:20,020 --> 00:08:23,020
As Peking Times, you fueled the rumors

170
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:25,260
and had this published.

171
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:27,900
Have your CEO known about it?

172
00:08:30,460 --> 00:08:31,940
Now I know it.

173
00:08:31,940 --> 00:08:33,500
Mr. Xue, Mr. Xue.

174
00:08:35,620 --> 00:08:36,740
(Xue Qianshan)

175
00:08:36,740 --> 00:08:37,500
Is this Mr. Du
(Xue Qianshan)

176
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:38,659
(Xue Qianshan)

177
00:08:38,659 --> 00:08:40,140
who wrote reviews of theatric performance?
(Xue Qianshan)

178
00:08:43,539 --> 00:08:44,220
Exactly.

179
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:45,860
It’s me.

180
00:08:46,180 --> 00:08:47,140
Indeed.

181
00:08:47,740 --> 00:08:48,380
Mr. Du.

182
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:50,220
Please.

183
00:08:59,220 --> 00:09:00,100
He has quite the temper.

184
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:01,260
Let me see.

185
00:09:08,260 --> 00:09:10,420
You want to publish the article

186
00:09:10,420 --> 00:09:12,820
to deny rumors of Shang Xirui.

187
00:09:16,740 --> 00:09:17,660
No offense,

188
00:09:18,220 --> 00:09:18,900
but in this way,

189
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,460
it seems you do this to serve private interests.

190
00:09:22,380 --> 00:09:23,940
Besides, I have read the article

191
00:09:25,060 --> 00:09:26,420
and find it not riveting.

192
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:29,980
Our readers may not like it.

193
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:33,380
Well, Mr. Xue,

194
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:35,060
please tell me

195
00:09:35,820 --> 00:09:37,580
what do your readers like?

196
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:41,220
They usually like

197
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:43,540
gossips of celebrities

198
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:45,380
or fascinating anecdotes.

199
00:09:48,940 --> 00:09:49,580
Fine.

200
00:09:50,620 --> 00:09:53,580
Since you know your readers so well,

201
00:09:54,420 --> 00:09:56,460
I wish nothing but

202
00:09:57,020 --> 00:09:58,860
great sales and loads of money

203
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:00,820
for your newspaper.

204
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,660
Mrs. Cheng, you got up so early.

205
00:10:14,540 --> 00:10:15,820
I didn’t sleep last night.

206
00:10:16,340 --> 00:10:17,740
Is Mrs. Cao back?

207
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:20,060
She came back at three in the morning,

208
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:21,820
and said she will skip lunch.

209
00:10:24,980 --> 00:10:26,220
Only one bowl of porridge is prepared?

210
00:10:26,340 --> 00:10:27,500
Chacha’er has eaten?

211
00:10:27,940 --> 00:10:28,740
Yes, she did.

212
00:10:33,380 --> 00:10:34,060
Mrs. Cheng.

213
00:10:35,420 --> 00:10:38,700
Mrs. Cheng, someone of the freight agency

214
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:41,660
came and said our silk is of high-value

215
00:10:41,660 --> 00:10:43,340
and wanted final payment.

216
00:10:43,420 --> 00:10:45,060
They block our door,

217
00:10:45,060 --> 00:10:46,700
make a scene there

218
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:50,300
and said our imported wine is of wrong year.

219
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:52,420
They refuse to leave and…

220
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:53,460
Okay, stop.

221
00:10:53,580 --> 00:10:55,020
Mr. Cheng often goes on business trips.

222
00:10:55,020 --> 00:10:57,140
How could you be unable to deal with it?

223
00:10:58,780 --> 00:11:00,620
To know the price of cargo,

224
00:11:00,620 --> 00:11:03,300
just check the order list.

225
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:05,300
Don’t you understand?

226
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:07,180
They just came to make a scene.

227
00:11:08,220 --> 00:11:09,660
Rumor has it that

228
00:11:09,660 --> 00:11:11,140
Mr. Cheng has been killed by bandits

229
00:11:11,140 --> 00:11:12,940
when he went on errands.

230
00:11:13,260 --> 00:11:14,220
Recently,

231
00:11:14,220 --> 00:11:16,580
people often come poking around

232
00:11:17,460 --> 00:11:19,780
and want to sabotage.

233
00:11:20,260 --> 00:11:21,060
I think

234
00:11:21,060 --> 00:11:23,380
those at the door are an advance party.

235
00:11:25,060 --> 00:11:26,900
Since we moved to Peking,

236
00:11:26,900 --> 00:11:28,340
they have been envious of us.

237
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:31,140
They pretend to respect

238
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:32,420
and fear Mr. Cheng,

239
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:35,020
but would make troubles when there is sign of change.

240
00:11:35,620 --> 00:11:38,380
But Mr. Cheng has really gone missing.

241
00:11:38,380 --> 00:11:40,180
They are taking advantage of us being vulnerable.

242
00:11:40,340 --> 00:11:41,140
Mrs. Cheng,

243
00:11:41,620 --> 00:11:43,300
you can’t let them be like this.

244
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:45,340
You must come up with a solution.

245
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:49,620
Mr. Ma.

246
00:11:50,020 --> 00:11:51,820
I’m your regular patron

247
00:11:51,820 --> 00:11:54,420
and won’t bother without reason.

248
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:55,340
But this time,

249
00:11:55,340 --> 00:11:57,460
the goods are of such high quality

250
00:11:57,460 --> 00:11:58,700
that I can’t surrender more profits.

251
00:11:59,420 --> 00:12:00,500
You could look at the goods.

252
00:12:00,820 --> 00:12:01,780
Take the silk over here.

253
00:12:02,940 --> 00:12:03,900
Please look at it.

254
00:12:04,420 --> 00:12:05,300
The fabric,

255
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:08,940
weaving and color.

256
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:10,540
It is perfect in every way.

257
00:12:10,860 --> 00:12:12,540
It’s great. Yeah.

258
00:12:13,220 --> 00:12:14,500
After receiving silk of such good quality,

259
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:17,620
Cheng’s freight agency

260
00:12:17,620 --> 00:12:19,140
pretends to be ignorant

261
00:12:19,140 --> 00:12:20,460
and wants to deny final payment.

262
00:12:21,660 --> 00:12:23,180
Can you imagine that?

263
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:23,900
Really?

264
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:24,780
What’s more,

265
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:27,060
about the wine I bought from you.

266
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:28,700
Take one bottle.

267
00:12:30,980 --> 00:12:33,260
Look, the year is wrong.

268
00:12:33,940 --> 00:12:34,660
Take a look.

269
00:12:34,660 --> 00:12:35,660
Look at it. Look.

270
00:12:36,620 --> 00:12:37,100
Take a look.

271
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:37,820
It’s true.

272
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:38,700
The year is wrong.

273
00:12:38,780 --> 00:12:39,780
Tell me how would you deal with it?

274
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:40,900
Yeah, could we still trust you

275
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:42,220
and buy from you in the future?

276
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:42,940
You should deal with it.

277
00:12:42,940 --> 00:12:44,180
What are you gonna do?

278
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:45,220
What about our business?

279
00:12:45,220 --> 00:12:46,060
Right.

280
00:12:46,060 --> 00:12:47,780
We are also doing business with you.

281
00:12:48,460 --> 00:12:49,420
Okay, okay.

282
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:50,740
Listen,

283
00:12:51,380 --> 00:12:52,380
well,

284
00:12:53,020 --> 00:12:55,540
I can’t decide this.

285
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:57,140
Please don’t be too hard.

286
00:12:57,380 --> 00:12:58,620
You will have the issue dealt with

287
00:12:58,620 --> 00:13:00,980
after my boss comes back.

288
00:13:01,780 --> 00:13:02,740
Your boss?

289
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:05,540
Your boss has gone missing for days.

290
00:13:05,540 --> 00:13:07,140
We don’t even know if he is alive.

291
00:13:07,140 --> 00:13:07,540
Right.

292
